Pre-Game Insights: The Brooklyn Nets will have a slight advantage in this matchup despite playing on the road.
Brooklyn has covered the number in 10 of its last 15 played on the road and that trend will continue on Wednesday.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Brooklyn Nets are 12-20 and 4th in the Atlantic division, 11 games behind the first-place Boston Celtics.
The Toronto Raptors are 7-25 and last in the Atlantic division, 16 games behind the first-place Celtics.
Others: Cam Thomas is leading Brooklyn in scoring with an average of 24.7 points per game and Cameron Johnson is second with an average of 19.1 points per game.
